didate C: strengths: very conscientious (reliability), can make correct decisions quickly, understands complicated technology. Weaknesses: difficulty communicating ideas, egocentric, not willing to further education. No calmness evidence.\n\nCandidate D: strengths: responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously. Weaknesses: know-it-all, hot temper, loner. No explicit calmness.\n\nThus B still best due to explicit reliability and calmness. Interpersonal issues are significant but can be mitigated. Others lack calmness or reliability. So we vote B.\n\nWe might ask other agents if they have any positive teamwork evidence for B, but we already asked earlier. Now maybe ask if any agent has any additional info on Candidate A's reliability or calmness, but we already asked and got none. So maybe we can ask if any agent has any positive teamwork evidence for Candidate D or C, but we have no such info. Could ask if any agent knows about Candidate D's calmness under pressure beyond \"responds adequately\". But we already asked and got none. So maybe we can ask if any agent has any info about Candidate A's reliability or calmness, but we already asked and got none. So maybe we can ask about any additional attributes not yet mentioned for any candidate, but the list is exhaustive.\n\nThus we can finalize our assessment and vote. Provide reasoning and maybe note remaining uncertainties (lack of positive teamwork for B). Provide final vote.\n\nWe must output PUBLIC_MESSAGE and METADATA_JSON with agent \"agent_2\". Let's craft."}
